    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="887"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/893, 894</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Nicaraguan Legation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>[The following paraphrases of telegrams exchanged between the Nicaraguan
                        Minister and the President of Nicaragua were left at the Department by the
                        Minister September 10 and 12, respectively.]</p>
                </quote>
                <p rend="center">[Translations]</p>
                <p>Department of State would be much pleased if the Government of Nicaragua would
                    use its good offices toward a friendly settlement of the differences between
                    Aguilar Barquero, “Designado” in charge of <pb facs="0964" n="862"
                        xml:id="pg_862"/> the Executive Power of Costa Rica and Acosta, by
                    endeavoring to have the latter’s forces enter San José without arms so as to
                    avoid any possible conflict and smooth the situation.</p>
                <closer>[No signature indicated]</closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1919</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Don Julio Acosta cheerfully accepted. Will leave this evening for San José
                        with his friends without arms [<hi rend="italic">unarmed</hi>].</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chamorro</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
